.TH ASTRAL 1 "2025-11-26" "Astral 5.3.1.6" "Astral Package Manager"
.SH NAME
astral \- minimal POSIX package manager for Astaraxia
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBastral\fR [\fIglobal options\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Astral is a minimal POSIX-compliant package manager designed for Astaraxia Linux. It runs on any system with \fB/bin/sh\fR, from servers to embedded devices.
.SH VERSION
Astral v5.3.1.6 Main (2025-11-26)
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Package Management
.TP
\fB-S\fR, \fB--Sync\fR \fIpkg\fR
Install or upgrade package from AOHARU repository
.TP
\fB-SA\fR, \fB--Sync-Asura\fR \fIpkg\fR
Install package from ASURA community overlay
.TP
\fB-C\fR, \fB--Compile\fR \fIpkg\fR
Build package from local recipe
.TP
\fB-R\fR, \fB--Remove\fR \fIpkg\fR
Remove installed package
.TP
\fB-r\fR, \fB--RemoveDep\fR \fIpkg\fR
Remove package and orphaned dependencies
.TP
\fB--autoremove\fR
Remove all orphaned packages
.TP
\fB--resume\fR \fIpkg\fR
Resume interrupted build
.TP
\fB--parallel-build\fR \fIpkgs\fR
Build multiple packages in parallel
.TP
\fB--parallel-remove\fR \fIpkgs\fR
Remove multiple packages in parallel
.SS Query & Information
.TP
\fB-s\fR, \fB--search\fR \fIpkg\fR
Search for packages in repositories
.TP
\fB-I\fR, \fB--info\fR \fIpkg\fR
Show detailed package information
.TP
\fB--inspect\fR, \fB-Ins\fR \fIpkg\fR
Inspect raw recipe contents
.TP
\fB-ll\fR, \fB--list-installed\fR
List all installed packages
.TP
\fB-D\fR, \fB--Deps\fR \fIpkg\fR
Show dependency tree for package
.TP
\fB-Dc\fR, \fB--DepCheck\fR
Check for broken dependencies
.TP
\fB--preview\fR \fIpkg\fR
Preview installation (packages + dependencies)
.TP
\fB-w\fR, \fB--why\fR \fIpkg\fR
Show why package is installed
.TP
\fB-W\fR, \fB--world\fR
List explicitly installed packages
.TP
\fB--host-check\fR \fIpkg\fR
Test if package is provided by host system
.TP
\fB--host-deps\fR
Show all host dependencies
.SS Package Holds
.TP
\fB--hold\fR \fIpkg\fR
Prevent package from being upgraded
.TP
\fB--unhold\fR \fIpkg\fR
Remove hold from package
.TP
\fB--list-held\fR
List all held packages
.SS System Operations
.TP
\fB--Upgrade-All\fR
Upgrade all installed packages
.TP
\fB-u\fR, \fB--Update\fR [\fIrepo\fR]
Update repository index (aoharu, asura, or both)
.TP
\fB-Cc\fR, \fB--Clean-Cache\fR
Clean uninstalled package cache
.TP
\fB-RI\fR, \fB--rebuild-index\fR
Rebuild file ownership index
.TP
\fB--chroot\fR \fIdir\fR
Chroot into specified directory
.SS Safety & Security
.TP
\fB--on\fR \fIfeature\fR
Enable safety feature (script-check, collision, ghost, checksum, mask, signature, audit, secure-download, file-integrity, merkle, cert-pin)
.TP
\fB--off\fR \fIfeature\fR
Disable safety feature
.TP
\fB--safety-status\fR
Show status of all safety features
.TP
\fB--import-key\fR \fIurl\fR
Import GPG repository key
.TP
\fB--verify-sig\fR \fIfile\fR
Verify GPG signature of file
.SS Advanced GPG Security
.TP
\fB--gpg-gen-key\fR \fIn\fR
Generate new GPG signing key
.TP
\fB--gpg-list-keys\fR
List managed GPG keys
.TP
\fB--gpg-set-trust\fR \fIid\fR \fIlevel\fR
Set key trust level (unknown|never|marginal|full|ultimate)
.TP
\fB--gpg-revoke\fR \fIkey\fR
Generate revocation certificate
.TP
\fB--gpg-rotate\fR \fIold\fR \fInew\fR
Rotate signing key
.TP
\fB--gpg-wot\fR
Build Web of Trust trust graph
.SS Certificate Pinning
.TP
\fB--pin-cert\fR \fIhost\fR[:\fIport\fR]
Pin HTTPS certificate
.TP
\fB--verify-cert\fR \fIhost\fR
Verify pinned certificate
.SS File Integrity (FIM)
.TP
\fB--fim-record\fR \fIfile\fR
Record file hash for integrity monitoring
.TP
\fB--fim-check\fR \fIfile\fR
Check file integrity
.TP
\fB--fim-scan\fR
Scan all tracked files
.SS Audit Trail
.TP
\fB--audit-query\fR
Query audit log
.TP
\fB--audit-verify\fR \fIrecipe\fR
Verify recipe audit trail
.SS Lock & Transactions
.TP
\fB--lock-info\fR
Show current lock status
.TP
\fB--lock-test\fR
Test lock system
.TP
\fB--transactions\fR [\fIstatus\fR]
List transactions (all|active|committed)
.TP
\fB--rollback\fR \fIid\fR
Rollback a transaction
.TP
\fB--recover\fR
Recover incomplete transactions
.SS Testing & Diagnostics
.TP
\fB--test\fR [\fImode\fR]
Run test suite (all|quick)
.TP
\fB--validate\fR \fIpkg\fR
Validate recipe file
.TP
\fB--verify-integrity\fR \fIpkg\fR
Verify installed package file integrity
.TP
\fB--verify-reproducible\fR \fIpkg\fR
Verify package builds reproducibly
.TP
\fB--graph-deps\fR \fIpkg\fR
Generate .dot dependency graph
.TP
\fB--cleanup-temp\fR
Clean temporary build directories
.TP
\fB--count\fR [\fIrepo\fR]
Show package counts (aoharu|asura|local|installed|all)
.TP
\fB--use\fR [\fIpkg\fR]
Show USE flags (global or for specific package)
.SS Service Management
.TP
\fBstart\fR \fIservice\fR
Start service (auto-detects init system)
.TP
\fBstop\fR \fIservice\fR
Stop service
.TP
\fBrestart\fR \fIservice\fR
Restart service
.TP
\fBenable\fR \fIservice\fR
Enable service at boot
.TP
\fBdisable\fR \fIservice\fR
Disable service at boot
.TP
\fBstatus\fR \fIservice\fR
Show service status
.SS Advanced Features
.TP
\fB--ccache-stats\fR
Show ccache statistics
.TP
\fB--ccache-clear\fR
Clear ccache
.TP
\fB--list-virtuals\fR
Show virtual package providers
.TP
\fB--mask\fR \fIpkg\fR [\fIop ver\fR]
Mask package version
.TP
\fB--unmask\fR \fIpkg\fR
Unmask package
.TP
\fB--config\fR
Show current configuration
.TP
\fB-SE\fR, \fB--show-env\fR
Show build environment
.SS Maintenance
.TP
\fB-U\fR, \fB--self-update\fR [\fIbranch\fR]
Update Astral itself (main|testing|bleeding)
.TP
\fB-V\fR, \fB--Version\fR
Show version information
.SS World Set Management
.TP
\fB--world-add\fR \fIpkg\fR
Add package to world set
.TP
\fB--world-remove\fR \fIpkg\fR
Remove package from world set
.TP
\fB--world-show\fR
Show world set
.TP
\fB--world-sets\fR
Show available sets (@system, @world)
.TP
\fB--world-depclean\fR
World-aware dependency cleaning
.TP
\fB--calc-system\fR
Calculate @system set
.SS Configuration
.TP
\fB--astral-stars-create\fR
Create default astral.stars config
.TP
\fB--astral-stars-edit\fR \fIfile\fR
Edit config and reload
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--dir\fR \fIDIR\fR
Installation root (default: /)
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--force\fR
Force operation (bypass conflicts)
.TP
\fB-n\fR, \fB--dry-run\fR
Preview without making changes
.TP
\fB-y\fR, \fB--yes\fR
Auto-confirm installation (skip prompt)
.TP
\fB-q\fR, \fB--quiet\fR
Suppress informational output
.TP
\fB-p\fR, \fB--pretend\fR
Show what would be done, no changes made
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--verbose\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB--json\fR
Output in JSON format (works with -s, -I, -ll)
.TP
\fB--check-version\fR
Check if astral itself has an update
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBASTRAL_DEBUG\fR
Enable debug mode (set to 1)
.TP
\fBVERBOSE\fR
Enable verbose output (set to 1)
.TP
\fBDEBUG_MODE\fR
Enable debug logging
.TP
\fBSTORE_DIR\fR
Content-addressed package store (default: /astral/store)
.TP
\fBRECIPES_DIR\fR
Local recipes directory (default: /usr/src/astral/recipes)
.TP
\fBCACHE_SRC\fR
Source cache directory (default: /var/cache/astral/src)
.TP
\fBDB_DIR\fR
Database directory (default: /var/lib/astral/db)
.TP
\fBCFLAGS\fR, \fBCXXFLAGS\fR, \fBLDFLAGS\fR
Build flags
.TP
\fBMAKEFLAGS\fR
Make flags (default: -j\fInproc\fR)
.SH FILES
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/make.conf\fR
Main configuration file
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/astral.stars\fR
Advanced configuration
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/package.mask\fR
Masked packages
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/package.provide\fR
Provided packages
.TP
\fB/var/lib/astral/db/\fR
Package database
.TP
\fB/var/cache/astral/src/\fR
Source cache
.TP
\fB/var/log/astral/\fR
Log files
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Install a package
\fBastral -S neofetch\fR
.SS Search for packages
\fBastral -s neofetch\fR
.SS List installed packages
\fBastral -ll\fR
.SS Upgrade all packages
\fBastral --Upgrade-All\fR
.SS Update repository index
\fBastral -u\fR
.SS Remove a package
\fBastral -R neofetch\fR
.SS Show package info
\fBastral -I neofetch\fR
.SS View dependency tree
\fBastral -D neofetch\fR
.SS Enable verbose output
\fBastral -v -S neofetch\fR
.SS Dry-run install
\fBastral -n -S neofetch\fR
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR astral-stars (5),
.BR make.conf (5)
